<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10013920771355></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10013920771355><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=10013920771355>RE: LVL 16</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=10013920771355#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=5743><span id= >Duttak</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 25th 12:27 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>16th is a good time to head over to High Hold pass, if you're patient, though I'd leave at around 19th-20th.&nbsp;&nbsp;The patience is because sometimes the line o get into a group there can be quite long, since there are really only two spawnpoints, orcs and gnolls.  If you decide not to do that, Oasis is still good, and you can start hunting over in the Lake of ill Omen in kunark.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
